dct_description_sm: Relief shown by contours, spot heights, and hachures. Depths shown by soundings. "Contour interval 10 meters. heights in meters, depths in fathoms at nearly lowest low water." Three classes of roads or trails, two classes of railroads, areas of vegetation and cultivation are shown. Some buildings are named. "Korean names transcribed according to the McCune-Reischauer system: Japanese forms of Korean names (in parenthesis) transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) system." Map shows administrative boundaries; three classes of roads or trails; two classes of railroads; and areas of vegetation and cultivation. Some buildings are named. "5-45." Military grid. Includes Japanese - Korean - English glossary of used terms. Key to precincts. Alternate title: Chinnamp'o, Korea. In upper left margin: Korea city plans 1:10,000. Polyconic projection. Relief shown by 10 meter contour interval and spot elevation. Depth shown by fathoms. Korean names transcribed according to the McCune-Reischauer system. Japanese forms of Korean names (in parenthesis) transcribed according to the Hepburn (Romaji) system. With a glossary. AMS 1.
dct_publisher_sm: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
